    I have many outdoor cameras. But I was looking for a small, wireless, battery powered, inexpensive camera to point at my critter feeder (rabbit, squirrels, birds, ducks, etc). At first, I got a vision well camera (B0B5GRGB58) but the image quality in the shade was very dark for some reason. Poor wide dynamic range? Bug? Not sure. So I returned it and got this one. Wow! The difference is night and day (pun intended). Excellent image quality in light and dark. Intelligent, full color or black and white night vision. Amazing night time image. Good motion detection and free humanoid detection. Extremely long battery life on a single charge. The application appears to be the same exact full featured application as my other cameras (Cloud Edge, Zumimall, Rebluum). Very easy to use and notifies you of any firmware updates. Out of the blue the manufacturer sent me a free solar charger. Thanks again! Simply Amazing product. EDIT 3.28.25: Motion detection does not work behind window glass, for some reason.

    I recently purchased the battery-operated security camera from ieGeek, and I must say it has exceeded my expectations in every way. This camera is a stellar addition to my home security setup, offering both convenience and reliability.

    Build Quality (5/5): The first thing that struck me about this camera is its exceptional build quality. It feels sturdy and well-made, capable of withstanding various weather conditions. The camera's durability gives me confidence that it will continue to operate flawlessly over the long term, even when exposed to the elements.

    Picture Quality (5/5): The ieGeek security camera boasts an impressive picture quality. The 2k resolution provides clear, crisp images both during the day and at night. The night vision feature is particularly remarkable; it captures detailed footage in low-light conditions, ensuring that my property is monitored 24/7 without missing a beat. I'm truly impressed by the camera's ability to deliver such high-quality visuals.

    Ease of Access (5/5): Accessing the camera feed is a breeze thanks to the ieGeek app. Setting up the camera and connecting it to the app was a straightforward process, and the user-friendly interface makes it easy to view the live feed, review recordings, and adjust settings from my smartphone or tablet. The real-time alerts ensure I'm promptly informed of any suspicious activity around my home, providing me with peace of mind even when I'm away.

    Battery Life (4/5): While the battery life is generally good, I've found that it can vary depending on the frequency of motion detection alerts and live streaming. However, it's worth noting that the camera comes with a USB-C port, which means I can have it plugged in to an outlet or connected to a solar cell. This minimizes downtime and keeps my property protected at all times.

    Conclusion:

    The ieGeek battery-operated security camera has truly impressed me with its robust build quality, exceptional picture clarity, and ease of access via the user-friendly app. The minor consideration regarding battery life is outweighed by the camera's overall performance. I highly recommend this security camera to anyone looking to enhance their home security with a top-notch device.

    Was looking for cameras to provide video protection for front and rear of house. The good reviews of these i Geek cameras led me to buying a twin camera pack (for a very good price!). Cameras arrived very quickly and on opening the box I was not disappointed. The cameras... See more
    Was looking for cameras to provide video protection for front and rear of house. The good reviews of these i Geek cameras led me to buying a twin camera pack (for a very good price!). Cameras arrived very quickly and on opening the box I was not disappointed. The cameras are are heavy and well built and certainly seem good quality. Pack comes with ball joint mounting brackets and wall fixings included. Instructions are pretty well written and easy to follow. I had both cameras up and running in 5 minutes after downloading the app from the i Geek website. Once installed I spent a few minutes looking through the options and settings to familiarise myself with the operation and features of the camera. I would recommend anyone purchasing these cameras to do the same as there are quite a few options available. The cameras were set up to my WiFi network and checked for WiFi connection in the intended location for mounting. Using the app you can monitor the signal strength and indeed the live video stream - great for ensuring you have a reliable connection from the camera. After confirming connection working all that was needed was to fix the cameras in their final position and final settings for motion detection etc. The cameras are working well and motion detection is excellent. I have logged into the cameras from my phone from areas well away from home and had no problem with live streams or controlling the cameras remotely. i Geek customer service is excellent with prompt answers to questions not related to camera operation. I have also had emails from them asking if all is well and do i need assistance - I find this reassuring there is a company checking all is well and replying to questions.
    Was looking for cameras to provide video protection for front and rear of house. The good reviews of these i Geek cameras led me to buying a twin camera pack (for a very good price!). Cameras arrived very quickly and on opening the box I was not disappointed. The cameras are are heavy and well built and certainly seem good quality. Pack comes with ball joint mounting brackets and wall fixings included. Instructions are pretty well written and easy to follow. I had both cameras up and running in 5 minutes after downloading the app from the i Geek website. Once installed I spent a few minutes looking through the options and settings to familiarise myself with the operation and features of the camera. I would recommend anyone purchasing these cameras to do the same as there are quite a few options available. The cameras were set up to my WiFi network and checked for WiFi connection in the intended location for mounting. Using the app you can monitor the signal strength and indeed the live video stream - great for ensuring you have a reliable connection from the camera. After confirming connection working all that was needed was to fix the cameras in their final position and final settings for motion detection etc. The cameras are working well and motion detection is excellent. I have logged into the cameras from my phone from areas well away from home and had no problem with live streams or controlling the cameras remotely.
    i Geek customer service is excellent with prompt answers to questions not related to camera operation. I have also had emails from them asking if all is well and do i need assistance - I find this reassuring there is a company checking all is well and replying to questions.
